<subSubSection id="48D355CA8EA5FF2B48A7541EFE2BFB7E" pageId="235" pageNumber="236" type="description">
<paragraph id="007606418EA5FF2B48A7541EFAB2FB9A" blockId="235.[151,1436,818,1383]" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">
<emphasis id="32BDDA538EA5FF2B48A7541EFE3FFCBB" bold="true" box="[151,410,818,843]" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">Description of female</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA5FF2B499C541EFDB8FCBA" box="[428,541,818,842]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">Plate 68A</figureCitation>
): fully winged; length 3.0–4.0 mm. Totally reddish, except antennal segments 1–3, 7–8 and part of 9 yellow. Antenna clavate. Head shiny, almost hairless, smooth, finely punctate; occipital carina complete; OL more than twice as long as POL; mandible quadridentate, with one rudimentary tooth between two posterior teeth. Scutum, scutellum and metanotum shiny, smooth, almost hairless, finely punctate. Notauli incomplete, hardly distinct, absent in posterior third of scutum. Propodeum reticulate rugose, with two lateral pointed apophyses (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA5FF2B494A54CAFE4EFC0E" box="[378,491,998,1022]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">Plate 68A</figureCitation>
); posterior surface with two complete longitudinal keels. Fore wing with two dark transverse bands; stigmal vein strongly curved; pterostigma short and narrow. Protarsal segments 
<quantity id="C731ABA48EA5FF2B4CD15326FA8DFBD2" box="[1249,1320,1034,1058]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="10.16" metricValueMin="2.54" pageId="235" pageNumber="236" unit="in" value="2.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="1.0">1–4 in</quantity>
following proportions: 15:4:3:12. Enlarged claw (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA5FF2B4A6A5302FD6FFBB6" box="[602,714,1070,1094]" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">Plate 68B</figureCitation>
) with one tooth and one bristle. Segment 5 of protarsus (
<figureCitation id="98F21AC48EA5FF2B4D545302FF60FB9A" captionStart="PLATE 68" captionStartId="237.[151,233,1877,1900]" captionTargetBox="[192,1397,217,1816]" captionTargetId="figure-56@237.[166,1421,193,1856]" captionTargetPageId="237" captionText="PLATE 68. A. Holotype, dorsal view. Length 3.0 mm. B, C. Chelae, holotypes. A, B. Bocchus rubricus (from Olmi 1984). C. B. rubrithorax (from Olmi 2005a). Scale bar 0.17 mm for B and 0.20 mm for C." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5278613" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5278613/files/figure.png" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">Plate 68B</figureCitation>
) with one preapical lamella, two bristles and one distinct proximal prominence. Tibial spurs 1/1/1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="007606418EA5FF2B48F7535BFE2BFB7E" blockId="235.[151,1436,818,1383]" box="[199,398,1142,1167]" pageId="235" pageNumber="236">
